title: Boys water polo: Edison upsets No. 8 Capo Valley at Villa Park Classic
text:
Â· posted by DAN ALBANO 
Edison's boys water polo team notched a breakthrough victory Friday at the Villa Park Classic. 
The unranked Chargers upset the No. 8 Cougars, 12-11, in overtime in a third-round consolation match at El Toro. 
Alex Nathan (five goals) and Jake Moss (four) combined for nine goals for Edison (11-6). 
The loss could drop Capistrano Valley from its top spot in Division 3. Laguna Beach and Murrieta Valley, ranked second and third, respectively, play this morning at 10 at Murrieta Valley. 
Please send water polo news to Dan Albano at dalbano@ocregister.com More from Blog: OC Varsity
